  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop the<strong> shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>,<strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>then peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Drain the<strong> mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper and tear into small, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Wash the<strong> rocket </strong>and pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1673971356659-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1673971356659-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1673971356659-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1673971356659-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1673971356659-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the<strong> ultimate vegan burger patties</strong> with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>Henderson’s Relish</strong> (save the rest for later!) and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and give everything a good mix up (clean hands is the best way) – this is your <strong>meatball mixture</strong></p><p>Divide the <strong>meatball mixture</strong> into 2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4] </span>balls, then flatten into circles (big enough to enclose the mozzarella)</p><p>Split <strong>half</strong> the <strong>torn mozzarella </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) equally between each meatball</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1673971367381-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1673971367381-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1673971367381-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1673971367381-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1673971367381-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wrap the <strong>meatball mix</strong> around the filling to form 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> meatballs and seal them tightly on all sides so that there aren't any gaps – these are your <strong>meat-free</strong> <strong>meatballs</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>meat-free</strong> <strong>meatballs </strong>to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>and<strong> </strong>drizzle with a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven and cook for 12-15 min or until lightly golden and firm on top</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1673971377729-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1673971377729-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1673971377729-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1673971377729-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1673971377729-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped shallot </strong>to the pan with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until softened and slightly caramelised</p><p>Dissolve the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong>, the <strong>remaining Henderson's Relish</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the<strong> balsamic vinegar </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) and a generous pinch of<strong> sugar</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your<strong> balsamic stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
